HEADWORD: Pouparts ligament
<hw>Pou*part's" lig"a*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A
ligament, of fascia, extending, in most mammals, from the ventral side
of the ilium to near the symphysis of the pubic bones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poupeton</ent>⟦br⟧
